=== Fixes applied ===
Commit f47f5f2: mount helpLayout at /help so the index outranks /help/$ wildcard
  - Root cause (1 fix, 6 symptoms): TanStack v1.169 `isFrameMoreSpecific`
    prefers deeper frames when statics/dynamics/index-ness are equal.
    With pathless `_helpLayout` and absolute `/help/...` child paths, the
    catch-all `/help/$` (depth 3) silently outranked the static index
    `/help` (depth 2) — `/help` resolved to the empty catch-all route,
    `<Outlet/>` rendered nothing inside `<article class="prose">`,
    and the catch-all's `beforeLoad` redirect-to-/help looped infinitely
    (each Link to=/help re-emitting the `Generated path … did not match`
    dev warning).
  - Fix: drop `id: '_helpLayout'`, mount the layout at `path: '/help'`,
    make children use TanStack-canonical relative shapes:
      * index entry → `path: '/'` (true INDEX node, beats sibling WILDCARD)
      * anchors/stubs/redirects → relative paths (`workflow/overview`, …)
      * catch-all → `path: '$'` (matches under /help/ only, NOT /help)
    Side-effect: route IDs change (auto-derived, no explicit id).
    All 6 lazy wrappers + router.test.tsx updated.
  - Resolved F1/F2 (article.prose visibility), F5/F6 (catch-all redirect),
    F8/F9 (mobile sidebar aria-label).

Commit 1082a69: tighten KbdHint locator and seed pairing in spec
  - F3/F4: `page.addInitScript` seeds PairingSchema record in
    localStorage BEFORE first goto, so /index route's beforeLoad doesn't
    redirect to /onboarding (where useGlobalShortcuts isn't mounted).
  - F7: scope locator to `article.prose span.font-mono` with exact-match
    text regex (`/^R$/`), so the mobile sidebar h3 "REPOSITORIES" doesn't
    win the `getByText('R').first()` race.

=== Console health ===
- console.error events: 0 (assertion held).
- TanStack `Generated path … did not match` warning flood: GONE
  (was symptomatic of the same matcher bug — now resolved at root).

=== Follow-up (NOT blocking T9) ===
- useGlobalShortcuts modifier-bail (`if (e.shiftKey) return`) prevents
  real-browser `?` keypresses (US-layout Shift+/) — Playwright's
